  "text": "Patients with LBBB are known to have an abnormal conduction pattern, associated with abnormal perfusion images. When this is taken into account, patients with LBBB are reported to have a similar prognosis after normal SPECT to patients without LBBB [CITATION_1] . Although the prognosis seemed worse, with MACE in 7.7 % of LBBB patients, compared with 2.6 % in non-LBBB patients, no difference in MACEfree survival was found. However, the small cohort of 52 LBBB patients limits the extrapolation of results and therefore we advise clinicians to be cautious when reviewing normal SPECT in LBBB patients.",
